Feature: US-TOOL-01 Establish Process for Periodic Review and Refinement of .gitignore
  As an AI Team Member,
  I want a defined process for periodically reviewing and refining `.gitignore`,
  So that codebase indexing remains optimal and irrelevant files are not version controlled.

  Scenario: Scheduled .gitignore Review at Sprint Start
    Given it is the beginning of a new sprint
    When ES checks the sprint initiation checklist
    Then ES MUST initiate a `.gitignore` file review with SET.

  Scenario: .gitignore Review and Update Procedure
    Given ES has initiated a `.gitignore` review with SET
    When ES and SET examine the project structure and current `.gitignore` content
    And they identify new log files (`*.newlog`) that should be ignored
    Then SET updates the `.gitignore` file to include `*.newlog`
    And SET commits the changes to `.gitignore`

  Scenario: .gitignore Review - No Changes Needed
    Given ES has initiated a `.gitignore` review with SET
    When ES and SET examine the project structure and current `.gitignore` content
    And they determine no new patterns or modifications are needed
    Then the review is documented as complete with no changes made to `.gitignore`.

  Scenario: Adding a Complex .gitignore Pattern with Rationale
    Given ES and SET are reviewing `.gitignore`
    And they decide to add a complex pattern `temp/[a-f0-9]*/` to ignore specific temporary hashed directories
    When SET updates the `.gitignore` file
    Then SET SHOULD add a comment `# Ignore temporary hashed directories generated by X tool` above the pattern. 